Bermuda suffered extensive powercuts after it was battered by Hurricane Gonzalo but it escaped the catastrophic damage and death toll that many had feared.

Much of the Atlantic archipelago was without electricity this morning and many roads were impassable due to downed trees and debris.

Only minor injuries were reported, however, Bermuda officials said.

