Gonzalo approached Bermuda as a Category 3 storm then weakened to Category 2 strength just before coming ashore with sustained winds of 110mph 

The last major hurricane to hit Bermuda, which is located approximately 600 miles of the coast of North Carolina, was Fabian in 2003, which caused $100million in damage.

The storm is currently continuing its path up the Atlantic and some forecasters believe its tail end will reach Britain this week.

